Print overview of stock-and-flow model

summary.sdbuildR_xmile.Rd

Print summary of stock-and-flow model, including number of stocks, flows, constants, auxiliaries, graphical functions, macros, custom model units, and use of delay functions. Also prints simulation specifications.

Usage

# S3 method for class 'sdbuildR_xmile'
summary(object, ...)

Arguments

object

Stock-and-flow model of class sdbuildR_xmile

...

Optional arguments

See also

build()

Examples

sfm = xmile("SIR")
summary(sfm)
#> Your model contains:
#> * 3 Stocks: Susceptible, Infected, Recovered
#> * 2 Flows: Infection_Rate, Recovery_Rate
#> * 3 Constants: Total_Population, Effective_Contact_Rate, Delay
#> * 2 Auxiliaries: Beta, Lambda
#> * 0 Graphical Functions
#> * 0 Custom model units
#> * 0 Macros
#> 
#> Simulation time: 0.0 to 20.0 seconds (dt = 0.01)
#> Simulation settings: solver euler in R
